article.headline: Norfolk State 63, Howard 48
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Derrick Smith scored 14 of his 21 points in the second half as Norfolk State rallied from a halftime deficit to defeat Howard 63-48 Monday night. Ryan Grier contributed 11 of his 15 points in the second half for the Spartans (10-16, 9-8 Mid-East Athletic Conference). Howard led 26-24 at the break. Norfolk State took the lead for good at 41-39 on two free throws by Grier with 10:24 left. Louis Ford led Howard (6-20, 4-13) with 18 points, and James Wilkinson had five points and 12 rebounds.
